Siyamcela Sombambela has been sentenced to 25 years. He was convicted of the murders of Bernadine Frans, Miché Pienaar and Gizella Minnaar in Wolseley in 2020. Monique Mortlock has been following developments. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Siyamcela Sombambela has been sentenced to 25 years for the murders of three women. Bernadine Frans, Miché Pienaar and Gizella Minnaar were killed in Wolseley in 2020. WATCH: Wolseley Serial Killer | Sombambela sentenced to 25 years The families of the victims say the justice system has let them down. In his ruling, Judge Lister Nuku took into account the fact that Sombambela is a first-time offender, he pleaded guilty and he cooperated with police back in 2020 by showing them where he had buried two of his victims. * eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports.